Below is a two-round review of the provided `ClassicalCurveSale.sol` snippet.

## Round 1 — Defense verification

### Defense mechanisms

| Defense                         | Evidence                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               | Verdict      |                                                                                                                                         |              |
| ------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------ |
| Reentrancy lock                 | `lock` uses transient storage at `SWAP_LOCK_SLOT` and reverts on reentry (`ClassicalCurveSale.sol:906-917`). It is applied to `buy`, `buyExactIn`, `sell`, `sellExactOut`, `swapExactIn`, `swapExactOut` (`512`, `563`, `629`, `664`, `928`, `992`).                                                                                                                                                   | **Verified** |                                                                                                                                         |              |
| CEI pattern                     | `buy` updates `sold` / `raisedETH` before token/ETH transfers (`539-553`). `buyExactIn` does the same (`604-618`). `sell` updates state before token pull / ETH sends (`647-653`). `sellExactOut` also updates first (`706-712`).                                                                                                                                                                      | **Verified** |                                                                                                                                         |              |
| Graduation state guard          | `graduate()` checks `!c.graduated                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |              | c.seeded`then sets`c.seeded = true` before any external calls (`725-730`), ahead of burn, approval, ZAMM call, and refunds (`738-772`). | **Verified** |
| Hook caller check               | `beforeAction()` immediately rejects non-ZAMM callers: `if (msg.sender != address(ZAMM)) revert Unauthorized();` (`783-789`).                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | **Verified** |                                                                                                                                         |              |
| Creator fee routing enforcement | When `creatorFees[token].beneficiary != 0`, direct `swap()` is rejected and `sender` must equal `address(this)` (`811-815`). Routed swaps are the functions that call ZAMM from this contract (`949-953`, `971-973`, `1011-1013`, `1024-1026`, `1040`, `1050-1051`).                                                                                                                                   | **Verified** |                                                                                                                                         |              |
| CREATE2 salt binding            | `launch()` derives `_salt = keccak256(abi.encode(msg.sender, name, symbol, salt))` before `create2` (`188-195`), so a third party cannot squat the same deterministic address with the same user salt.                                                                                                                                                                                                 | **Verified** |                                                                                                                                         |              |
| Overflow guards                 | Only `virtualReserve` is range-checked (`314`). But `_configure()` stores multiple fields as `uint128(...)` without any explicit bounds checks: `cap`, `startPrice`, `endPrice`, `raisedETH` init, `graduationTarget`, `virtualReserve`, `lpTokens` (`328-343`), especially `startPrice`/`endPrice`/`graduationTarget`/`lpTokens` at `336-341`. The claimed guard does not cover all persisted fields. | **Violated** |                                                                                                                                         |              |
| Graduation target validation    | `_configure()` does compare the **input** `graduationTarget` against `maxETH` (`316-325`), but the persisted runtime value is `uint128(graduationTarget)` (`339`). So the validated value and the effective stored value can diverge for oversized inputs.                                                                                                                                             | **Violated** |                                                                                                                                         |              |

